'''José Pedro Balmaceda Pascal''' (born 2 April 1975) is a <!--Do NOT add any links, please see WP:OVERLINK.-->Chilean and American<!--No hyphen, as that may imply his ethnicity.--> actor. He began his career guest-starring on various television shows before rising to prominence for portraying [[Oberyn Martell]] on the [[Game of Thrones (season 4)|fourth season]] of the [[HBO]] fantasy series ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' (2014) and [[Javier Peña]] on the [[Netflix]] biographic crime series ''[[Narcos]]'' (2015–2017). He has played the [[The Mandalorian (character)|title character]] on the [[Disney+]] ''[[Star Wars]]'' series ''[[The Mandalorian]]'' since 2019, reprising his role in the spin-off series ''[[The Book of Boba Fett]]''. He is also set to play the lead role of [[Joel (The Last of Us)|Joel]] in [[The Last of Us (TV series)|''The Last of Us'']]. Outside of television, he has appeared in the films ''[[The Adjustment Bureau]]'' (2011), ''[[Bloodsucking Bastards]]'' (2015), ''[[The Great Wall (film)|The Great Wall]]'' (2016), ''[[Kingsman: The Golden Circle]]'' (2017), ''[[The Equalizer 2]]'' (2018), ''[[Triple Frontier (film)|Triple Frontier]]'' (2019), ''[[Wonder Woman 1984]]'' (2020) and ''[[The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent]]'' (2022).

==Early life and education==
{{see also|Allende family|Balmaceda family}}

José Pedro Balmaceda Pascal was born in [[Santiago]], [[Chile]] on 2 April 1975.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Pedro Pascal Profile |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/pedro_pascal |access-date=2 April 2022 |website=Rotten Tomatoes |language=en |archive-date=2 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220402214627/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/pedro_pascal |url-status=live }}</ref> His mother, Verónica Pascal Ureta, was a child psychologist and his father, José Balmaceda, is a fertility doctor;<ref>{{cite news |last=Ito |first=Robert |title=A Lethal Prince, Even if a Bit Clumsy: Pedro Pascal Becomes Red Viper on 'Game of Thrones' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/30/arts/television/pedro-pascal-becomes-red-viper-on-game-of-thrones.html?_r=0 |access-date=27 May 2014 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=28 March 2014 |archive-date=12 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112020115/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/30/arts/television/pedro-pascal-becomes-red-viper-on-game-of-thrones.html?_r=0 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="nytsarticle">{{cite web |last=Koblin |first=John |title=Pedro Pascal: Making It at 41 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/fashion/mens-style/pedro-pascal-great-wall-game-of-thrones-narcos-late-success.html |access-date=4 July 2019 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=3 February 2017 |archive-date=29 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040531/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/fashion/mens-style/pedro-pascal-great-wall-game-of-thrones-narcos-late-success.html |url-status=live}}</ref> he has an older sister, Javiera,<ref>{{cite web |title="Narcos" star Pedro Pascal on the mystery of Pablo Escobar's death | website=[[YouTube]] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HC5G0bsSQtw |access-date=3 November 2020 |archive-date=29 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040511/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HC5G0bsSQtw |url-status=live}}</ref> and two younger siblings, Nicolás, and [[Lux Pascal]], an actress and transgender activist in Chile.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.t13.cl/noticia/entretencion/Lucas-Balmaceda-el-hermano-del-chileno-de-Game-of-Thrones-que-llego-a-remecer-Los-80 |title=Lucas Balmaceda, el hermano del chileno de Game of Thrones que llegó a remecer Los 80 |website=t13.cl |access-date=13 January 2018 |archive-date=11 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111204523/https://www.t13.cl/noticia/entretencion/Lucas-Balmaceda-el-hermano-del-chileno-de-Game-of-Thrones-que-llego-a-remecer-Los-80 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Pedro Pascal Sweetly Supports His Sister Lux After She Comes Out as a Trans Woman: 'Mi Corazón' |url=https://people.com/movies/pedro-pascal-supports-sister-lux-comes-out-trans-woman/ |website=People |date=9 February 2021 |access-date=12 February 2021 |archive-date=11 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211212045/https://people.com/movies/pedro-pascal-supports-sister-lux-comes-out-trans-woman/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Pascal's mother was the cousin of [[Andrés Pascal Allende]], the nephew of socialist [[President of Chile|President]] [[Salvador Allende]] (through his sister [[Laura Allende|Laura]]) and leader of the [[Revolutionary Left Movement (Chile)|Movement of the Revolutionary Left]], an urban guerrilla movement dedicated to the overthrow of the [[Military dictatorship of Chile (1973–1990)|military dictatorship]] of [[Augusto Pinochet]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.latercera.com/noticia/pedro-pascal-punto/ |title=Pedro Pascal, en su punto |website=La Tercera |date=1 September 2017 |access-date=10 January 2021 |archive-date=24 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224073623/https://www.latercera.com/noticia/pedro-pascal-punto/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

According to Pascal, his parents were devout followers of Allende and active in resistance groups against the Pinochet dictatorship.<ref name="reddit">Pascal, Pedro. (25 May 2014). Reddit. [https://www.reddit.com/r/IAmA/comments/26gtvt/i_am_actor_pedro_pascal_i_play_oberyn_in_game_of I am actor Pedro Pascal. I play Oberyn in Game of Thrones, Ask me anything.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201110003947/https://www.reddit.com/r/IAmA/comments/26gtvt/i_am_actor_pedro_pascal_i_play_oberyn_in_game_of/ |date=10 November 2020 }}</ref> Because of this, nine months after his birth, Pascal's family sought refuge in the Venezuelan Embassy in Santiago, and were later granted political asylum in [[Denmark]].<ref name=OrangeCoast>{{cite news |last=Broeske |first=Pat H. |title=The Viper Prince |url=http://www.orangecoast.com/features/2014/04/28/the-viper-prince |access-date=27 May 2014 |publisher=Orange Coast |date=28 April 2014 |archive-date=2 June 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140602035249/http://www.orangecoast.com/features/2014/04/28/the-viper-prince |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="people"/> The family ultimately moved to the United States, and Pascal was raised in [[Orange County, California]] and [[San Antonio]], [[Texas]].<ref>{{cite news |last=McIntyre |first=Gina |title='Game of Thrones': Red Viper actor Pedro Pascal hates spoilers too |url=http://herocomplex.latimes.com/tv/game-of-thrones-red-viper-actor-pedro-pascal-hates-spoilers-too/ |access-date=27 May 2014 |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=12 May 2014 |archive-date=8 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908015642/https://herocomplex.latimes.com/tv/game-of-thrones-red-viper-actor-pedro-pascal-hates-spoilers-too/ |url-status=live}}</ref> By the time he was 8, his family was able to take regular trips back to Chile to visit his 34 first cousins.<ref name="variety">{{cite web |last=Vary |first=Adam B. |title=Pedro Pascal on Fame and 'The Mandalorian': 'Can We Cut the S— and Talk About the Child?' |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/pedro-pascal-the-mandalorian-star-wars-wonder-woman-1984-1234803468/ |access-date=1 January 2021 |website=Variety |date=14 October 2020 |archive-date=15 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201015194622/https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/pedro-pascal-the-mandalorian-star-wars-wonder-woman-1984-1234803468/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Pascal was involved in competitive swimming during his early years and took part in the state championships in Texas at the age of 11, but stopped competitive swimming after getting into drama class.<ref name="reddit"/>  He studied acting at the [[Orange County School of the Arts]], graduating in 1993, and [[New York University]]'s [[Tisch School of the Arts]], graduating in 1997.<ref name=OrangeCoast/><ref name="ETW">{{cite web |title=ETW Alumni |url=https://tisch.nyu.edu/drama/about/studios/experimental-theatre-wing/alumni |website=[[New York University]] |access-date=1 January 2021 |archive-date=19 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210119205137/https://tisch.nyu.edu/drama/about/studios/experimental-theatre-wing/alumni |url-status=live }}</ref>

== Career ==
Pascal has appeared in several television series, including ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'', ''[[The Good Wife]]'', ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]]'', ''[[The Mentalist]]'', and ''[[Graceland (TV series)|Graceland]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=''The Good Wife'' Actor Checks Into USA's ''Graceland'' in Major Arc |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/graceland-pedro-pascal-joins-386618 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |last=Ng |first=Philiana |access-date=30 May 2013 |date=5 November 2012 |archive-date=29 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040507/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/graceland-pedro-pascal-joins-386618 |url-status=live}}</ref> He appeared as kidnapper Reggie in the ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]'' episode "Weeping Willow" and appeared as Special Agent Greer in ''[[Law & Order: SVU]]'' episode "Smoked". He was cast in the pilot for the [[Wonder Woman (2011 TV pilot)|2011 ''Wonder Woman'' television adaptation]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Guthrie |first=Marisa |date=3 March 2011 |title=Pedro Pascal Joins NBC's 'Wonder Woman' Pilot |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/pedro-pascal-joins-nbcs-wonder-164014/ |access-date=18 July 2021 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date=18 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210718145651/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/pedro-pascal-joins-nbcs-wonder-164014/ |url-status=live }}</ref> but the show was never picked up. In June 2013, he was cast as [[Oberyn Martell]] in the [[Game of Thrones (season 4)|fourth season]] of the [[HBO]] series ''[[Game of Thrones]]''.<ref name="EW.com 28 June 2013">{{cite magazine |last=Hibberd |first=James |title=''Game of Thrones'' casts major season 4 role: Oberyn the Red Viper |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2013/06/28/thrones-red-viper-oberyn/ |access-date=30 June 2013 |magazine=Entertainment Weekly |date=28 June 2013 |archive-date=29 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040451/https://ew.com/article/2013/06/28/thrones-red-viper-oberyn/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Pascal stated that he was a huge fan of ''Game of Thrones'' before being cast as Oberyn and was ecstatic to join.<ref name="reddit"/> In 2015, Pascal was cast in the role of U.S. [[Drug Enforcement Administration|DEA]] agent [[Javier Peña]] in the [[Netflix]] original show ''[[Narcos]]''. In the movie ''[[Bloodsucking Bastards]]'' (2015), Pascal portrayed the vampire Max.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Miska |first1=Brad |title=INDIE'Bloodsucking Bastards' Turns Cast Into Vamps |url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/indie/3289705/bloodsucking-bastards-turns-cast-into-vamps/ |date=21 April 2014 |website=bloody-disgusting.com |access-date=7 June 2017 |archive-date=29 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040442/https://bloody-disgusting.com/indie/3289705/bloodsucking-bastards-turns-cast-into-vamps/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Pascal has extensive stage experience as both an actor and director; he received the Los Angeles Drama Critics Circle Award and [[Back Stage Garland Awards|Garland Award]] for his role in the [[International City Theater]] production of ''Orphans'', and has performed in classical and contemporary works. He has appeared [[Off-Broadway]] in ''Maple and Vine'' by [[Jordan Harrison]], ''Beauty of the Father'' by [[Nilo Cruz]], [[Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa]]'s ''Based on a Totally True Story'', Trista Baldwin's ''Sand'', [[David Greenspan]]'s ''Old Comedy'', [[Terrence McNally]]'s ''[[Some Men]]'', and [[Shakespeare in the Park (New York)|Shakespeare in the Park]]'s 2006 production of ''[[Macbeth]]''.<ref name="Theater Mania January 2012">{{cite web |last=Karam |first=Edward |title=Pedro Pascal Takes A Direct Approach |url=http://www.theatermania.com/new-york-city-theater/news/01-2012/pedro-pascal-takes-a-direct-approach_47987.html |website=Theater Mania |access-date=30 June 2013 |archive-date=29 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040458/https://www.theatermania.com/new-york-city-theater/news/pedro-pascal-takes-a-direct-approach_47987.html |url-status=live}}</ref> He is a member of New York City's [[LAByrinth Theater Company]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Company Members |url=http://www.labtheater.org/companymembers/memberslist.html |website=[[LAByrinth Theater Company]] |access-date=4 June 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019045129/http://www.labtheater.org/companymembers/memberslist.html |archive-date=19 October 2013}}</ref> Pascal made his Broadway debut in February 2019 in an adaptation of ''[[King Lear]]'' with [[Glenda Jackson]] and [[Ruth Wilson]].<ref>{{Cite web |last1=12 September |first1=David Canfield |last2=EDT |first2=2018 at 10:31 AM |title=Ruth Wilson, Pedro Pascal, more to star opposite Glenda Jackson in 'King Lear' on Broadway |url=https://ew.com/theater/2018/09/12/ruth-wilson-pedro-pascal-king-lear/ |access-date=15 April 2022 |website=EW.com |language=en |archive-date=15 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220415193039/https://ew.com/theater/2018/09/12/ruth-wilson-pedro-pascal-king-lear/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In April 2015, Pascal co-starred with [[Heidi Klum]] in the music video for [[Sia]]'s "[[Fire Meet Gasoline]]".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gordon |first1=Jeremy |title=Sia's "Fire Meet Gasoline" Used in Video Starring Heidi Klum, "Game of Thrones" Actor Pedro Pascal |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/59388-sias-fire-meet-gasoline-used-in-video-starring-heidi-klum-game-of-thrones-actor-pedro-pascal/ |website=[[Pitchfork Media]] |access-date=23 April 2015 |date=23 April 2015 |archive-date=29 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040539/https://pitchfork.com/news/59388-sias-fire-meet-gasoline-used-in-video-starring-heidi-klum-game-of-thrones-actor-pedro-pascal/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2017, he starred as Agent Whiskey in [[Matthew Vaughn]]'s ''[[Kingsman: The Golden Circle]]'' and as mercenary Pero<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 February 2017 |title=Pedro Pascal goes from 'Game of Thrones' to 'Great Wall' |url=https://www.dailynews.com/arts-and-entertainment/20170215/pedro-pascal-goes-from-game-of-thrones-to-great-wall |access-date=26 May 2022 |website=Daily News |language=en-US |archive-date=15 May 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170515170352/http://www.dailynews.com/arts-and-entertainment/20170215/pedro-pascal-goes-from-game-of-thrones-to-great-wall |url-status=live }}</ref> Tovar in ''[[The Great Wall (film)|The Great Wall]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt2034800/characters/nm0050959 |title=The Great Wall (2016) |website=IMDb |access-date=4 January 2020 |archive-date=29 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040511/https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2034800/characters/nm0050959 |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2018, Pascal co-starred as Dave York, the primary antagonist in the thriller sequel film ''[[The Equalizer 2]]''; the film starred [[Denzel Washington]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ford |first1=Rebecca |title='The Equalizer' Sequel Adds Pedro Pascal |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/equalizer-sequel-adds-pedro-pascal-1030230 |access-date=22 August 2017 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=21 August 2017 |archive-date=24 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824092247/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/equalizer-sequel-adds-pedro-pascal-1030230 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Since 2019, Pascal has portrayed the [[The Mandalorian (character)|title role]] in ''[[The Mandalorian]]'', the first live-action ''[[Star Wars]]'' television series, which debuted on [[Disney+]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/the-mandalorian-star-wars-pedro-pascal-talks-disney-streaming-series-1202501235/ |title='The Mandalorian' Targets Pedro Pascal For Title Role In Disney+ Series |last=Boucher |first=Geoff |website=Deadline |date=13 November 2018 |access-date=14 November 2018 |archive-date=13 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113232557/https://deadline.com/2018/11/the-mandalorian-star-wars-pedro-pascal-talks-disney-streaming-series-1202501235/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The same year, he starred as Francisco "Catfish" Morales in the Netflix heist drama ''[[Triple Frontier (film)|Triple Frontier]]''.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2017/07/netflix-triple-frontier-mark-wahlberg-charlie-hunnam-garrett-hedlund-pedro-pascal-1202126476/ |title=Netflix 'Triple Frontier' Eyes August Start; Mark Wahlberg, Charlie Hunnam, Garrett Hedlund, Pedro Pascal In Talks |last1=Fleming |first1=Mike Jr. |date=26 July 2017 |work=Deadline |access-date=30 July 2017 |archive-date=3 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211003071903/https://deadline.com/2017/07/netflix-triple-frontier-mark-wahlberg-charlie-hunnam-garrett-hedlund-pedro-pascal-1202126476/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He also played [[Maxwell Lord]] in the [[DC Extended Universe]] film ''[[Wonder Woman 1984]]'', directed by [[Patty Jenkins]]. Following delays due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]], the film was released to theaters and [[HBO Max]] on 25 December 2020.<ref name="PascalCast">{{cite news |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title='Narcos' Star Pedro Pascal Lands Key Role in 'Wonder Woman' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-sequel-narcos-1202738657/ |access-date=29 May 2018 |work=Variety |date=28 March 2018 |archive-date=29 March 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180329010138/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-sequel-narcos-1202738657/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Hex">{{cite web |title=Fandom twitter |url=https://twitter.com/getFANDOM/status/1187374105118609409 |website=Twitter |access-date=26 October 2019 |archive-date=29 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040441/https://twitter.com/getFANDOM/status/1187374105118609409 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In February 2021, Pascal was cast in the [[Judd Apatow]] film ''[[The Bubble (2022 film)|The Bubble]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=9 February 2021 |title=Judd Apatow Sets All-Star Cast For New Netflix Comedy 'The Bubble'; Karen Gillan, Keegan-Michael Key, Maria Bakalova & Pedro Pascal Among 9 Set To Join Ensemble |url=https://deadline.com/2021/02/judd-apatow-sets-netflix-the-bubble-karen-gillian-keegan-michael-key-pedro-pascal-and-leslie-mann-among-those-set-to-join-ensemble-1234690118/ |access-date=12 April 2021 |website=Deadline |language=en-US |archive-date=11 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211111043352/https://deadline.com/2021/02/judd-apatow-sets-netflix-the-bubble-karen-gillian-keegan-michael-key-pedro-pascal-and-leslie-mann-among-those-set-to-join-ensemble-1234690118/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The film premiered on Netflix on 1 April 2022. Pascal co-starred with [[Nicolas Cage]] in the comedy ''[[The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent]]'' which premiered at SXSW 2022 in April.<ref>{{Cite web |last=DeFore |first=John |date=13 March 2022 |title=Nicolas Cage in 'The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent': Film Review {{!}} SXSW 2022 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/nicolas-cage-in-the-unbearable-weight-of-massive-talent-film-sxsw-2022-1235110212/ |access-date=15 April 2022 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date=15 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220415191536/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/nicolas-cage-in-the-unbearable-weight-of-massive-talent-film-sxsw-2022-1235110212/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In February 2021, Pascal was cast in the lead role of [[Joel (The Last of Us)|Joel Miller]] for the upcoming [[HBO]] adaptation of ''[[The Last of Us (TV series)|The Last of Us]]''.<ref name="Deadline Pascal" /> It was reported Pascal will receive $600,000 per episode.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Otterson |first1=Michael Schneider,Joe |last2=Schneider |first2=Michael |last3=Otterson |first3=Joe |date=18 August 2021 |title=Streaming Boom Keeps TV Salaries at Heady Levels: Here's What Kate Winslet, Jason Sudeikis and More Are Earning |url=https://variety.com/2021/tv/news/tv-salaries-2021-kate-winslet-jason-sudeikis-succession-1235043291/ |access-date=15 April 2022 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date=18 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210818232156/https://variety.com/2021/tv/news/tv-salaries-2021-kate-winslet-jason-sudeikis-succession-1235043291/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In November 2022, he was cast in ''[[Freaky Tales (film)|Freaky Tales]]'', to be directed by [[Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title=Pedro Pascal, Ben Mendelsohn, Jay Ellis And Jack Champion Among Those Joining Ensemble Of eOne And Macro's ''Freaky Tales'' From Ryan Fleck And Anna Boden |url=https://deadline.com/2022/11/pedro-pascal-ben-mendelsoh-jay-ellis-jack-champion-eone-macros-freaky-tales-ryan-fleck-anna-boden-1235174116/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=16 November 2022 |date=November 16, 2022}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Pascal is [[Multilingualism|bilingual]] in English and Spanish.

Pascal moved to [[New York City]] in 1993 and has lived there since.<ref name=OrangeCoast/> In 1995, while Pascal was at NYU, his father was indicted by a federal grand jury relating to events at a fertility clinic he ran with two other men.<ref name="nytsarticle"/><ref name=":0">{{cite news |last1=Sims |first1=Calvin |title=Fertility Clinics in Chile: A Tale of a Doctor Fleeing U.S. Law |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/04/26/world/fertility-clinics-in-chile-a-tale-of-a-doctor-fleeing-us-law.html |agency=nytimes.com |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=26 April 1996 |access-date=12 February 2021 |archive-date=5 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105191300/https://www.nytimes.com/1996/04/26/world/fertility-clinics-in-chile-a-tale-of-a-doctor-fleeing-us-law.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Following this, his father, mother and two youngest siblings returned to Chile; Pascal contends that his father did nothing wrong.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Koblin |first=John |date=3 February 2017 |title=Pedro Pascal: Making It at 41 |work=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/fashion/mens-style/pedro-pascal-great-wall-game-of-thrones-narcos-late-success.html |access-date=17 May 2022 |archive-date=29 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040531/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/fashion/mens-style/pedro-pascal-great-wall-game-of-thrones-narcos-late-success.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Farinh |first=Ricardo |date=2 October 2020 |title=De refugiado a estrela da televisão: a jornada de Pedro Pascal para chegar a Hollywood |work=NiT |url=https://www.nit.pt/cultura/de-refugiado-estrela-da-televisao-jornada-de-pedro-pascal-para-chegar-hollywood |access-date=17 May 2022 |archive-date=20 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220720034740/https://www.nit.pt/cultura/de-refugiado-estrela-da-televisao-jornada-de-pedro-pascal-para-chegar-hollywood |url-status=live }}</ref>

Pascal's mother committed [[suicide]] in 1999.<ref name="nytsarticle" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Gilson |first=Hilary |date=15 June 2010 |title=José Pedro Balmaceda (1948- ) |url=https://embryo.asu.edu/pages/jose-pedro-balmaceda-1948 |access-date=4 May 2022 |archive-date=19 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220419155718/https://embryo.asu.edu/pages/jose-pedro-balmaceda-1948 |url-status=live }}</ref> Following her death, Pascal began using his mother's surname professionally both in honor of her and because he said Americans had difficulty pronouncing his first surname, Balmaceda.<ref name="people">{{cite web |title=The Mandalorian's Pedro Pascal Credits His Success to His Mom, Who Died Before He Became Famous |url=https://people.com/tv/the-mandalorian-pedro-pascal-credits-his-success-to-his-mom/ |date=13 November 2020 |access-date=1 January 2021 |website=People |archive-date=12 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201212035519/https://people.com/tv/the-mandalorian-pedro-pascal-credits-his-success-to-his-mom/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="variety" />

Pascal is an outspoken advocate of [[LGBT rights by country or territory|LGBTQ+ rights]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ennis |first=Dawn |title=This Is The Way 'The Mandalorian' Cast Gets Personal On Social Media |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dawnstaceyennis/2020/10/30/this-is-the-way-the-mandalorian-cast-gets-personal-on-social-media/ |access-date=10 April 2022 |website=Forbes |language=en |archive-date=11 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220411001948/https://www.forbes.com/sites/dawnstaceyennis/2020/10/30/this-is-the-way-the-mandalorian-cast-gets-personal-on-social-media/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He was supportive of his sister Lux when she came out as [[transgender]]; she said: “He has been an important part of this. He is also an artist and has been a guide. He was one of the first to give me the things that formed my identity."<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 February 2021 |title=Pedro Pascal Sends Love To Sister Coming Out As Transgender |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/pedro-pascal-sister-coming-out-as-transgender_n_6023eac3c5b6d78d444b623e |access-date=11 April 2022 |website=HuffPost |language=en |archive-date=11 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220411002729/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/pedro-pascal-sister-coming-out-as-transgender_n_6023eac3c5b6d78d444b623e |url-status=live }}</ref>

He is close friends with [[Sarah Paulson]]<ref name=Interview>{{cite web |url=https://www.interviewmagazine.com/culture/pedro-pascal |title=Pedro Pascal |author=Sarah Paulson |author-link=Sarah Paulson |date=18 September 2014 |access-date=11 February 2021 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116150127/https://www.interviewmagazine.com/culture/pedro-pascal |archive-date=16 January 2021}}</ref> and [[Oscar Isaac]].<ref name=Fansided>{{cite web |url=https://culturess.com/2021/01/02/internet-celebrates-star-wars-friendship-pedro-pascal/ |title=The internet is losing it over this Star Wars celebrity friendship |last=Mullen |first=Amanda |date=2 January 2021 |access-date=11 February 2021 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210102190328/https://culturess.com/2021/01/02/internet-celebrates-star-wars-friendship-pedro-pascal/ |archive-date=2 January 2021}}</ref><ref name=ET>{{cite news |last=Calvario |first=Liz |date=1 January 2021 |title='Star Wars' Pals Oscar Isaac and Pedro Pascal Ring in the New Year Together: See Festive Pic |url=https://www.etonline.com/star-wars-pals-oscar-isaac-and-pedro-pascal-ring-in-the-new-year-together-see-festive-pic-158474 |work=[[Entertainment Tonight]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130074244/https://www.etonline.com/star-wars-pals-oscar-isaac-and-pedro-pascal-ring-in-the-new-year-together-see-festive-pic-158474 |archive-date=30 January 2021 |access-date=11 February 2021}}</ref> He endorsed [[President of Chile|Chilean President]] [[Gabriel Boric]] in the [[2021 Chilean presidential election]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 November 2021 |title=Pedro Pascal hace público con una fotografía su apoyo a Gabriel Boric |url=https://www.t13.cl/noticia/elecciones-2021/tendencias/pedro-pascal-apoyo-gabriel-boric-elecciones-segunda-vuelta-23-11-2021 |last= |first= |access-date=29 November 2021 |work=[[Teletrece]] |archive-date=29 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211129212634/https://www.t13.cl/noticia/elecciones-2021/tendencias/pedro-pascal-apoyo-gabriel-boric-elecciones-segunda-vuelta-23-11-2021 |url-status=live }}</ref> Pascal has said that he is [[Agnosticism|agnostic]],<ref>{{Cite journal |date=23 February 2017 |title=Bad Hombre Pedro Pascal |journal=Solar Magazine}}</ref> and a [[Social liberalism|liberal]].<ref>{{Cite journal |date=24 August 2017 |title=Narco's Pedro Pascal |journal=ShortList Magazine}}</ref>

